2. LLMs

*Large Language Models are part of a foundation model, are pre-trained on large amounts of data with self-supervision which means that the model learns from patterns in the data in a way that produces adaptable outputs. 

#Components of an LLM

I. Data:  Large Language models are trained on large datasets of text, such as books, articles and conversations. Parameter is a value that a model can change independently as it learns, the more parameters a model has, the more complex it can be.

II. Architecture: Is a neural network, for GPT(Generative Pre-trained Transformer) this is a Transformer, the transformer architecture enables the model to handle sequences of data like sentences or lines of code. Transformers are designed to understand the context of each word in a sentence by considering it in relation to every other word. This allows the model to build a comprehensive understanding of the sentence structure and meaning of the words in it. 

III. Training: Then, the architecture is trained on all the large amounts of gathered data. During training the model learns to predict the next word in the sentence. For ex: when the user types The school is, the model will start to predict with something like insect, and after each iteration, the model adjusts its internal parameters and try to reduce the differences between the predictions and the actual outcome. The model repeats this until it can generate full meaningful sentences. 

IV .Fine Tuning: Models can be@ fine tuned on a smaller, specific dataset. It’s done so that the model can perform a specific task more accurately. This is what allows a model to become an expert at a specific task. 

